It is also possible to output using custom markup; see the
[Index→Custom Markup action xix_ref_act_x_mark.html] and the
[Custom Markup Dialog xix_ref_dlg_markup.html]. To output in a custom
markup invoke this action, and type the custom markup's custom extension
(e.g., ~F.ucp~E), after the filename in the file chooser dialog.

If you want to import an index (in ~X's XML Interchange Format
~F.ximl~E, or in Index Data Exchange Format ~F.ixml~E), see the
[File→Import action xix_ref_act_f_imp.html].

Some output formats have format-specific output options that can be set,
for which, see the
[Output Options Dialog's Format Specific Tab xix_ref_dlg_out_fmt.html].

-------------------------
Note that some other tools use the terms “save as” or “generate” for
outputting an index.

See also [Third-Party Products xix_3rdparty.html].

